uchea.svg}}/{{flagicon image|Flag_of_the_State_of_Cambodia.svg}} [[Cambodia]]\n|[[Democratic Kampuchea]]\n|17 April 1975\n|22 June 1982\n|{{ayd|1975|4|17|1982|6|22}}\n|[[Khmer Rouge]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|Constitutionally a Marxist\u2013Leninist state from 1975 to 1991, but it was not internationally recognized by some countries following the [[Cambodian\u2013Vietnamese War]].<ref name=kiernanxix>Kiernan, B. (2004) ''How Pol Pot came to Power''. New Haven: Yale University Press, p. xix</ref><ref name=\"ReferenceA\">Margaret Slocomb, ''The People's Republic of Kampuchea, 1979-1989: The revolution after Pol Pot'' {{ISBN|978-974-9575-34-5}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[People's Republic of Kampuchea]]\n|10 January 1979\n|1 May 1989\n|{{ayd|1979|1|10|1989|5|1}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[People's Revolutionary Party of Kampuchea]]\n|-\n|[[People's Republic of Kampuchea#Transition and State of Cambodia (1989\u20131992)|State of Cambodia]]\n|1 May 1989\n|23 October 1991\n|{{ayd|1989|5|1|1991|10|23}}\n|-\n|Total\n|17 April 1975\n|23 October 1991\n|{{ayd|1975|4|17|1991|10|23}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon image|Flag of the People's Republic of Congo.svg}} [[Republic of the Congo|Congo]]\n|[[People's Republic of the Congo]]\n|3 January 1970\n|15 March 1992\n|{{ayd|1970|1|3|1992|3|15}}\n|[[Congolese Labor Party]]\n|Presidential oath: \"I swear allegiance to the Congolese people, to the Revolution and to the [[Congolese Labor Party]]. I shall undertake, while guided by [[Marxism\u2013Leninism|Marxist-Leninist principles]], [...] to devote all my strength to the triumph of the proletarian ideals\".<ref>Van Maarseveen, Henc; Van Der Tanq, Ger (21 November 1978). ''Written Constitutions: A Computerized Comparative Study''. BRILL. [https://books.google.com/books?id=2fEeaVS1I0wC&pg=PA125 p. 125].</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|{{flag|Czechoslovakia}}\n|[[Czechoslovak Republic (1948-1960)|Czechoslovak Republic]]\n|9 June 1948\n|11 July 1960\n|{{ayd|1948|6|9|1960|7|11}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Communist Party of Czechoslovakia]]\n|row