y/r?frd%2Fcstdy%3A%40field%28DOCID+et0127%29 |archive-date=2004-10-29 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Workers' Party of Ethiopia]]{{refn|From 12 September 1984.|group=\"nb\"}}\n|-\n|[[People's Democratic Republic of Ethiopia]]\n|22 February 1987\n|27 May 1991\n|{{ayd|1987|2|22|1991|5|27}}\n|-\n|Total\n|28 June 1974\n|27 May 1991\n|{{ayd|1974|6|28|1991|5|27}}\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|East Germany}}\n|[[German Democratic Republic]]\n|7 October 1949\n|3 October 1990\n|{{ayd|1949|10|7|1990|10|3}}\n|[[Socialist Unity Party of Germany]]\n|Section 1, Article 1: \"The German Democratic Republic is a socialist state of workers and peasants. It is the political organization of the working people of town and country under the leadership of the working class and its [[Socialist Unity Party of Germany|Marxist-Leninist party]]\".<ref>{{cite constitution|article=1|section=1|country=the German Democratic Republic|language=|ratified=7 October 1974|url=|accessdate=}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flag|Grenada}}\n|[[People's Revolutionary Government (Grenada)|People's Revolutionary Government]]\n|13 March 1979\n|25 October 1983\n|{{ayd|1979|3|13|1983|10|25}}\n|[[New Jewel Movement]]\n|People's Law Number Two: \"The People's Revolutionary Government, PRG, is hereby established as of Tuesday 13 March 1979, in accordance with the sovereign will of the Grenadian people, and in it shall be vested of executive and legislative power\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thegrenadarevolutiononline.com/declaration.html|title=Declaration of the Grenada Revolution|work=The Grenada Revolution Online|date= 25 March 1979|accessdate=August 16, 2019}}</ref><br /><br />The [[New Jewel Movement]] considered themselves a Marxist\u2013Leninist [[vanguard party]].<ref>[http://www.thegrenadarevolutiononline.com/manifesto.html \"The Manifesto of the New Jewel Movement\"], The Grenada Revolution Online.</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|{{flag|Hungary}}\n|rowspan=2|[[Hungarian People's Republic]]\n|rowspan=2|20 August 1949\n|rowspan