{"title_page": "The Sky Is Pink", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 film directed by Shonali Bose}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Sky Is Pink\n| image          = The Sky Is Pink.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Shonali Bose]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Ronnie Screwvala]]\n* [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]]\n* Kilian Kerwin\n* [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]]\n* Madhu Chopra\n}}\n| screenplay         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Shonali Bose]]\n* Nilesh Maniyar\n* <small>(Additional)</small>\n* [[Juhi Chaturvedi]]\n* <small>(Hindi dialogues)</small>\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Priyanka Chopra Jonas\n* [[Farhan Akhtar]]\n* [[Zaira Wasim]]\n* [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]]\n}}\n| narrator       = Zaira Wasim\n| music          = {{Plainlist|\n'''Songs:'''\n* [[Pritam]]\n'''Score:'''\n* [[Mikey McCleary]]\n}}\n| cinematography = {{Plainlist|\n* Kartik Vijay\n* Nick Cooke\n}}\n| editing        = Manas Mittal\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[RSVP Movies]]\n* Roy Kapur Films\n* [[Purple Pebble Pictures]]\n*Ivanhoe Pictures\n}}\n| distributor    = RSVP Movies\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|09|13|[[Toronto International Film Festival|TIFF]]|2019|10|11|df=y|India}}\n| runtime        = 143 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/sky-pink-2019|title=The Sky Is Pink (2019)|publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=10 October 2019}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = \n| gross          = {{Estimation}} {{INR}}34.41 crore<ref name=\"box:bbh\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/box-office/|title=The Sky is Pink Box Office|website=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=25 October 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''The Sky Is Pink''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[biographical film]] written and directed by [[Shonali Bose]]. The film was co-produced by [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]], [[Ronnie Screwvala]] and [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]] under their production companies of [[RSVP Movies]], Roy Kapur Films and [[Purple Pebble Pictures]] in association with Ivanhoe Pictures. The film stars Chopra Jonas, [[Farhan Akhtar]], [[Zaira Wasim]], and [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]]. Based on the real life story of [[Aisha Chaudhary]] who was diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], the film tells the love story of her parents, Aditi and Niren, dealing with their daughter's illness.\n\nAditi Chaudhary approached Bose to make a film based on her daughter. Although intrigued by the story, Bose instead chose to depict the story of the couple from Aisha's point of view, focusing on their marriage and the effect of a child's illness on the lives of the parents and their relationship. Bose wrote the screenplay based on the details she has gathered through interviewing Aditi and Niren. Nilesh Maniyar wrote the additional screenplay while Hindi dialogue writing was done by [[Juhi Chaturvedi]]. Filming took place in Mumbai, London, Delhi and [[Andaman Islands|Andaman]]. [[Pritam]] composed the soundtrack and [[Gulzar]] wrote the lyrics for the songs.\n\nThe film premiered at the [[44th Toronto International Film Festival]] on 13 September 2019. It was released worldwide on 11 October 2019. ''The Sky Is Pink'' received generally positive reviews, with praise directed towards Bose's writing and direction and the performances. It did not perform well at the box office, grossing {{INR}}34.41 crore worldwide. The film received three [[Filmfare Awards]] nominations: [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Film|Best Film (Critics)]], [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] for Chopra Jonas and [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]] for Wasim.\n\n== Plot ==\n[[Aisha Chaudhary]] narrates the story of her parents, Moose (her mother) and Panda (her father) from [[afterlife]]. Aditi and Niren are a young couple who come from two different backgrounds. Aditi is from the posh end of the town, [[South Delhi]], where on another hand Niren is from a grounded middle-class family. The couple are shown to be in love, with \"an active sex life\" as Aisha's narration describes. The passionate and happy couple get married, and Aditi becomes pregnant with their first child Tanya, who dies within months of her birth due to the [[Severe combined immunodeficiency]] condition. Baby Tanya used to frequently become ill and, while Aditi was convinced it was a serious issue, Niren used to brush it off. Niren believed that negligence was the reason Tanya couldn't be treated sooner and blamed himself for the death of his child. As Aditi was mourning the death of her child, she was consoled by a Catholic church nun and decided to be baptised.\n\nAditi and Niren have a second child Ishaan. A few years later, Aditi bore their third child, another daughter, Aisha. They later learn that Aisha was born with the same Severe combined immunodeficiency condition as their first child, Tanya and Niren are heartbroken. After the doctors in Delhi give up on the treatment, the couple go to London where they learn that the disease could be treated by performing [[bone marrow transplant]]. However, they learn that the treatment is very costly. Niren starts working to earn the money while also asking for crowdfunding via a radio station. After several weeks, they learn that several people have donated money for Aisha's treatment. The surgery is successful but Aisha is kept under doctor's watch. Aditi decides to stay in London while Niren goes back to India with his family and his son Ishaan. Aditi grows overprotective of Aisha, over cleaning the apartment and other things to keep Aisha away from any potential infection. \n\nIshaan starts missing his mother while Niren is always thinking about Aditi and Aisha. This also starts affecting Aditi and Niren's relationship as Aditi is always occupied with Aisha and taking care of her. Months go by and Niren goes to London and asks Aditi to move back to India so that their relationship is not affected. He reasons with Aisha on the grounds that Aisha had gotten better and occasional doctor's visit can be done in India as well. Aditi tells him that they have to live here for a very long time as per doctor's recommendation till Aisha's condition is cured. The whole family moves here permanently till Aisha is cured. Niren's career grows in London and he becomes rich and their family becomes affluent.\n\nSeveral years later, Aisha has finally gotten better and Niren and Aditi decide to move back to India with their families. They shift to the outskirts of Delhi and buy an extravagant and massive bungalow. After a doctor's visit, Aditi and Niren learn that Aisha has been diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], a side effect of the chemotherapy that was done to cure the previous disease. With less time on Aisha's life, Aditi sets out to fulfill all of Aisha's dreams such as adopting a pet (which Aditi did not allow due to the risk of infection), seeing the aquatic life and writing a book, among other things. As Aisha's condition worsens, Aditi grows more and more overprotective and due to over stress, suffers a psychotic breakdown and is hospitalized. Aditi does everything in her power to make sure Aisha gets to see the first copy of her book before she dies. Later, Aisha passes away.\n\nAfter the death of Aisha, Aditi and Niren's relationship is strained. While living together, they grow apart and are constantly fighting with each other. Aditi still cannot accept Aisha's death and constantly brings her in their fights. At a party, Niren shows Aisha's secret video that he had found, a video she had made about her parents. Niren wants Aditi to move with him to London so that she can forget Aisha which she finds insulting as she does not want to let Aisha's memories fade, particularly the house. With anger, Niren leaves for London while Aditi stays back. Aditi later goes to meet Niren in London and they reconcile.\n\n== Cast ==\nThe cast has been listed below:<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/cast/|title=The Sky Is Pink||publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]] as Aditi Chaudhary\n* [[Farhan Akhtar]] as Niren Chaudhary\n* [[Zaira Wasim]] as [[Aisha Chaudhary]]\n* [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]] as Ishaan Chaudhary\n* Vidhaan Sharma as Young Ishaan\n* Manas Mittal as Anshu Tandon\n* Rajshri Deshpande as Anita Tandon\n* Lushin Dubey as Mrs. Tandon\n* Sunil Chitkara as Mr. Chaudhary\n* Nirupama Verma as Mrs. Chaudhary\n* Puja Sarup as Mohini\n* Gurpal Singh as Rj Arjun Gill\n* Sheena Khalid as Rita\n* Sudhanva Deshpande as Dr. Nirvick Gulati\n* Manisha Chudasama as Santoshi\n* Paras Rattan Sharda as Jeet\n* Salmin Sheriff as Dr. Batliwala\n* Rishi Deshpande as Tanya\u2019s Doctor\n* Virhi as Baby Tanya\n* Mala Hashmi as Christian Woman\n* Akshay Joshi as Store Assistant\n* Nargis Nandal as Pilot\n* Raabia Marici as Ishaan\u2019s Girlfriend\n{{Div col end}}\n\n== Production ==\n===Development and writing===\nThe production of the film started when [[Aisha Chaudhary]]'s mother Aditi approached [[Shonali Bose]] to make a film about her daughter. Chaudhary had seen the trailer of Bose's last film ''[[Margarita with a Straw]]'' (2015) thirty times and was eager to watch the film, saying \"I hope I live to see this film.\"<ref name=\"tnie\">{{cite news|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/oct/09/indian-culture-is-better-equipped-to-deal-with-grief-the-sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-2044820.html|title=Indian culture is better equipped to deal with grief: 'The Sky Is Pink' director Shonali Bose|last=Mitra|first=Shilajit|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=9 October 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"th\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/all-cinema-has-an-inherent-patriarchal-ideology/article29410318.ece|title=All cinema has an inherent patriarchal ideology: Shonali Bose|last=Namrata|first=Joshi|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=13 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> However, she passed away at the age of 18 after being diagnosed with [[Pulmonary fibrosis|pulmonary fibrosis]], two weeks after watching the trailer and never got to see the film. Nine months later, Aditi Chaudhary tracked down Bose who was then living in [[Los Angeles]]. Aditi was adamant as she only wanted Bose to tell the story of her daughter.<ref name=\"th\"/><ref name=\"ht\">{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-says-death-of-her-son-end-of-marriage-drew-her-to-the-story/story-otpNEnfTrDPR1OKaNeBWJJ.html|title=Sky is Pink director Shonali Bose says death of her son, end of marriage drew her to the story|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=10 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> Initially, they interacted over [[Skype]]. Later, Bose personally interviewed both Aditi and Niren Chaudhary for eight hours a day for two weeks to gather all the details.<ref name=\"tnie\"/><ref name=\"scroll\">{{cite news|url=https://scroll.in/reel/936799/the-sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-it-is-a-rare-couple-who-survive-the-death-of-their-child|title=\u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019 director Shonali Bose: \u2018It is a rare couple who survive the death of their child\u2019|last=Ramnath|first=Nandini|publisher=[[Scroll.in|Scroll]]|date=10 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> Bose said that \"They talked and cried and healed through the process of those narrations.\"<ref name=\"tnie\"/> Bose had said that she was drawn towards the story as she herself had lost her son so was she ready to explore the subject cinematically and bringing some of her own unique perspective to it.<ref name=\"th\"/><ref name=\"outlook\">{{cite news|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-shonali-bose-on-the-sky-is-pink-har-ek-ka-apna-sky-hota-hai-what-colour-is-your-sky/339168|title=Shonali Bose On \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019: \u201cHar Ek Ka Apna Sky Hota Hai. What Colour Is Your Sky?\u201d|last= Roy|first=Lachmi Deb|work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]|date=22 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> However, she was more interested in telling the story of Aditi and Niren, a couple, dealing with the illness of their child, saying \"I was drawn to the story, not of a heroic teenager defying death, but the parents who had to deal with it.\"<ref name=\"th\"/> Bose said she was \"intrigued and inspired\" by the Chaudharys' relationship, adding \"It is a rare couple who survive the death of their child.\"<ref name=\"scroll\"/> She said she wanted to explore \"what happens to a love story, to a marriage, when faced with the loss of a child\", explaining \"My own marriage ended when I lost my son. 80% of people\u2019s marriages end when they lose a child.\"<ref name=\"ht\"/><ref name=\"scroll\"/> She wanted to make an unusual romantic film and the lives of Aditi and Niren were exactly unusual like the film she wanted to make.<ref name=\"outlook\"/> In December 2018, Ivanhoe Pictures came on board to co-finance and co-produce the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/ivanhoe-pictures-priyanka-chopra-the-sky-is-pink-1203085471/|title=Ivanhoe Pictures Boards Priyanka Chopra\u2019s \u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019|last=Frater|first=Patrick|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=10 December 218|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBose began writing the screenplay based on the narration she had heard from the Chaudharys by approaching it as a love story of two people who fell in love when they were \"only 16 and now at 57 are still inseparable\" despite major tragedies that tear most couples apart.<ref name=\"scroll\"/><ref name=\"outlook\"/> Bose chose to tell the film from Aisha's point of view, focusing on 25 years of her parents' marriage.<ref>{{cite news |title=Priyanka Chopra: 'The Sky Is Pink' Has \"Moments Of Joy, Moments Of Tragedy\" \u2014 Toronto Studio|url=https://deadline.com/video/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shonali-bose-tiff-toronto/ |author=Blyth, Antonia |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=8 September 2019 |accessdate=14 September 2019 }}</ref> Nilesh Maniyar, a longtime collaborator of Bose, had also met Aditi and Niren and wanted to make a documentary about Aisha as he felt there was more to explore and saw Bose's film as very different than his, both projects being in different formats. Since Maniyar had also done his research on Aisha's life, Bose invited him to write the additional screenplay.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/the-sky-is-pink-writer-nilesh-maniyar-deconstructs-priyanka-chopras-psychotic-breakdown-scene-2367617.html|title=The Sky Is Pink Writer Nilesh Maniyar Deconstructs Priyanka Chopra's Psychotic Breakdown Scene|last=Negi|first=Shristi|publisher=3[[CNN News18]]|date=31 October 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"confirms\">{{cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/090718/priyanka-chopra-shonali-bose-abhishek-farhan-zaira-sky-is-pink-script.html|title=Priyanka confirms Shonali Bose\u2019s film, reveals title, mystery continues over hero|work=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|date=9 July 2018|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> [[Juhi Chaturvedi]] wrote the Hindi dialogues.<ref name=\"confirms\"/> Bose wanted to stay true to the real life events and depict them as it unfolded in their lives, without fictionalising or deflecting from actual incidents. She said \"The story, facts and events in the film are completely true. I wrote the script as close as possible to the truth. So, when deciding the look and feel of the film, I decided to stay with realism and be as authentic as possible.\"<ref name=\"th\"/><ref name=\"scroll\"/> While writing the script, Bose met with Aisha's family and friends and inquired everything about her. She also read Aisha's writing, including her emails to her brother and the artwork she had made. Bose revealed that feel connected with Aisha even though they never met.<ref name=\"scroll\"/> In handling the subject, Bose consciously chose to be realistic and avoid melodramatic and manipulative set-ups to express emotions.<ref name=\"th\"/> She said \"I am also very conscious of steering clear of melodrama and exploiting or manipulating you with overwrought emotions. I want you to feel what my characters feel but also give you space. This is part of my film form.\"<ref name=\"scroll\"/> In an interview with [[Scroll.in|Scroll]], Bose revealed that in early drafts, Aditi was the main protagonist as she was written to be the central figure in the story, but later strengthened Niren's role and they became equal in the final draft.<ref name=\"scroll\"/>\n\n[[Siddharth Roy Kapur]] had liked Bose's previous film and had expressed his desire to work with her.<ref name=\"rediff\">{{cite news|url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/report/sky-is-pink-required-big-stars/20191010.htm|title='Sky Is Pink required big stars'|last=Chhabra|first=Aseem|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|date=10 October 2020|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> After the acquisition of [[UTV Motion Pictures]] by [[The Walt Disney Company]], Kapur was appointed managing director of the company of [[The Walt Disney Company India]] in 2014 and produced several films under the new name as he had previously done with UTV. Kapur established his own company, Roy Kapur Films, in January 2017.<ref name=\"rediff\"/> When Bose found out about his new production house, she approached him with the script of ''The Sky Is Pink'' and Kapur picked it to be the first film under of his company.<ref name=\"rediff\"/><ref name=\"mint\">{{cite news|url=https://www.livemint.com/Consumer/vK8fluGeIY8nXR4h4b7RUO/Embracing-technology-is-the-only-way-to-remain-relevant-Sid.html|title=Embracing technology is the only way to remain relevant: Siddharth Roy Kapur|last=Sharma|first=Sanjukta|work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]|date=22 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> He said that he found the script wonderfully moving, told with wit, humour, depth and feeling.<ref name=\"mint\"/> As a part of a [[first look deal]] with [[RSVP Movies]], Kapur set the film there, thus collaborating with [[Ronnie Screwvala]], the ex-UTV Studio head, as producers.<ref name=\"rediff\"/>\n\n===Casting and characters===\nThe film's casting news first came out in May 2018 suggesting that [[Priyanka Chopra]], [[Abhishek Bachchan]] and [[Zaira Wasim]] had been cast in Bose's next untitled. The media reports suggested that Wasim was cast as Aisha Chaudhary, with Chopra and Bachchan playing her parents.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/abhishek-bachchan-and-priyanka-chopra-to-play-parents-to-zaira-wasim-1235853-2018-05-18|title=Abhishek-Priyanka to play Zaira Wasim's parents in Shonali Bose's film?|work=[[India Today]]|date=18 May 2018|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> A month later media reports claimed that [[Farhan Akhtar]] had replaced Bachchan and now he would be playing <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-farhan-akhtar-replaces-abhishek-bachchan-in-shonali-bose-s-next-to-star-opposite-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim-2629148|title=Farhan Akhtar replaces Abhishek Bachchan in Shonali Bose's next; to star opposite Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|date=25 June 2018|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> Chopra confirmed her involvement on 9 July 2018 by posting a picture of the script of ''The Sky Is Pink'' on her [[Instagram]] account, revealing the title of the film.<ref name=\"confirms\"/> The official announcement followed the next day, confirming Akhtar and Wasim's casting in the film.<ref name=\"announcement\">{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/farhan-akhtar-may-replace-abhishek-bachchan-in-shonali-boses-the-sky-is-pink-opposite-priyanka-chopra-4702601.html|title=Farhan Akhtar, Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim confirmed to star in Shonali Bose's The Sky Is Pink|publisher=[[Firstpost]]|date=10 July 2018|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> It is the second film to feature Chopra and Akhtar opposite each other after ''[[Dil Dhadakne Do]]'' (2015).<ref name=\"announcement\"/> [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]] was cast as Aisha's brother Ishaan after four rounds of auditions over a period of four months.<ref name=\"saraf\">{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/rohit-saraf-s-sky/cid/1710754|title=Rohit Saraf's sky|last=Paul|first=Ushnota|work=The Telegraph|date=11 October 2019|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> The film marked the return of Chopra to Bollywood films after three years as she was busy with her Hollywood work.<ref name=\"theweek\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/2019/10/03/Priyanka-Chopra-reveals-how-The-Sky-is-Pink-reminded-her-of-her-parents.html|title=Priyanka Chopra reveals how 'The Sky is Pink' reminded her of her parents|author=[[Press Trust of India]]|work=[[The Week (Indian magazine)|The Week]]|date=3 October 2019|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> After coming on board the film as an actor, Chopra asked her Kapur and Screwvala to join them as the producer as she believed in the film and wanted to take more responsibility of the film and learn about producing from them.<ref name=\"theweek\"/> Kapur and Screwvala, both frequent collaborators of Chopra (who had starred in several of their films under UTV), agreed to bring her as a producer, thus making ''The Sky Is Pink'' making the first Hindi film to be produced under Chopra's company [[Purple Pebble Pictures]].<ref name=\"theweek\"/>\n\nSaraf described his character Ishaan saying he is someone who becomes the pillar of the family during the tragedy. He revealed that portraying the character was delightful as he got to explore human emotions a lot more than he had before in his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/rohit-saraf-it-was-always-a-dream-to-work-with-priyanka-chopra-1607218-2019-10-08|title=Rohit Saraf: It was always a dream to work with Priyanka Chopra|last=Singh|first=Suhani|work=India Today|date=8 October 2019|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> Unlike the rest of the cast, Saraf was not not allowed to see the documented footage of the Chaudhary family as Bose thought he would not be able to take that well.<ref name=\"saraf\"/> To prepare for his character, Saraf had researched a lot about the Chaudhary family during the audition process. After his casting, he stopped his research and relied mostly on Bose's inputs on her advice and the collaborative efforts of the cast which he said enhanced his performance.<ref name=\"saraf\"/>\n\nSince the film spans 25 years, the characters of Aditi and Niren's looks undergo several transformations as they age. These changes were mostly accomplished by make-up and hair styling.<ref name=\"transformation\">{{cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-priyanka-chopra-jonas-and-farhan-akhtars-transformation-in-the-sky-is-pink/340216|title=Priyanka Chopra Jonas And Farhan Akhtar\u2019s Transformation In \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019|work=Outlook|date=9 October 2019|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> Chopra's hair inform the age of her character; when her character is young the hair is longer and it gets shorter as she ages in the film, short hair at 50. Akhtar's Character, when younger sports curly hair while is groomed when his character matures and is given mustache in the later portions of the film.<ref name=\"transformation\"/>\n\n===Filming===\nFilming began on 8 August 2018 in [[Mumbai]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.asianage.com/entertainment/bollywood/080818/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-farhan-and-zaira-begin-filming-for-shonali-boses-film.html |title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka, Farhan and Zaira begin filming for Shonali Bose's film |date=8 August 2018 |website=asianage.com |access-date=12 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://twitter.com/priyankachopra/status/1027046519424180224 |title=PRIYANKA on Twitter |work=Twitter |access-date=2018-10-26 |language=en}}</ref> The second schedule of the film began on 13 October 2018 in [[London]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bo4YizMgDCM |title=Priyanka Chopra on Instagram |website=Instagram |language=en |access-date=2018-10-26}}</ref> and wrapped on 17 October 2018. It was part of the [[Delhi]] schedule which wrapped in the last week of November 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BpB0xKshQ-x |title=Rohit Suresh Saraf on Instagram: \"It's a schedule wrap for #TheSkyIsPink. Thank you #London \ud83e\udde1\" |website=Instagram |language=en |access-date=2018-10-26}}</ref> The filming is completed on 11 March 2019 in [[Andaman Islands]]<ref name=\":p1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/mar/14/shooting-complete-for-priyanka-chopras-the-sky-is-pink-1950745.html |title=Shooting complete for Priyanka Chopra's 'The Sky Is Pink' |date=14 March 2019 |website=The New Indian Express}}</ref> A song was shot in June 2019 in Mumbai for the film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-to-return-to-mumbai-to-shoot-for-a-song-for-the-sky-is-pink-with-farhan-akhtar-and-zaira-wasim/articleshow/69258603.cms |title=Priyanka Chopra to return to Mumbai to shoot for a song for The Sky is Pink with Farhan Akhtar and Zaira Wasim |last=Lohana |first=Avinash |date=10 May 2019 |website=Mumbai Mirror}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = The Sky Is Pink\n| type         = soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Pritam]]\n| cover        = \n| border       = yes\n| alt          = \n| released     = 4 October 2019\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 21:08\n| language     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| label        = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = [[Chhichhore]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| year         = 2019\n| next_title   = [[Love Aaj Kal (2020 film)|Love Aaj Kal]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n}}\n\nThe film's music is composed by [[Pritam]] while lyrics are written by [[Gulzar]].<ref name=\"th\"/> It contains four original songs and a reprisal, with vocals provided by singers such as [[Arijit Singh]], [[Antara Mitra]], [[Arjun Kanungo]], [[Lisa Mishra]], Shashwat Singh, [[Jonita Gandhi]] and Sreerama Chandra.<ref name=\"itunes\"/> The soundtrack was released on 4 October 2019 by [[Zee Music Company]].<ref name=\"itunes\"/>\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline       = Track listing<ref name=\"itunes\">{{Cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/in/album/the-sky-is-pink-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1482434710|title=The Sky Is Pink (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)|publisher=[[iTunes]]|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n| total_length   = 21:28\n| extra_column   = Singer(s)\n| title1         = Dil Hi Toh Hai\n| extra1         = [[Arijit Singh]], [[Antara Mitra]]\n| music1         = [[Pritam]]\n| lyrics1        = Gilzar\n| length1        = 4:40\n| title2         = Nadaaniyaan\n| extra2         = [[Arjun Kanungo]], Lisa Mishra\n| music2         = Pritam\n| lyrics2        = Gulzar\n| length2        = 4:18\n| title3         = Zindagi\n| extra3         = Arijit Singh\n| music3         = Pritam\n| lyrics3        = Gulzar\n| length3        = 4:09\n| title4         = Pink Gulaabi Sky\n| extra4         = Shashwat Singh, [[Jonita Gandhi]]\n| music4         = Pritam\n| lyrics4        = Gulzar\n| length4        = 3:20\n| title5         = Dil Hi Toh Hai\n| note5          = Reprise\n| extra5         = Sreerama Chandra, Antara Mitra\n| music5         = Pritam\n| lyrics5        = Gulzar\n| length5        = 4:41\n}}\n\n== Marketing and release ==\nA first look was released on 23 July 2019. The poster was released on 8 September 2019, followed by a [[trailer (promotion)|trailer]] on 10 September by RSVP Movies.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=prwUFBsDRLk |title=The Sky Is Pink \u2013 Official Trailer \u2013 Priyanka C J, Farhan A, Zaira W, Rohit S \u2013 Shonali B \u2013 Oct 11 |date=10 September 2019 |website=YouTube |publisher=RSVP Movies}}</ref>\n\n''The Sky Is Pink'' premiered at the [[44th Toronto International Film Festival]] on 13 September 2019, and was theatrically released worldwide on 11 October.<ref name=\"toird\">{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/priyanka-chopras-the-sky-is-pink-set-for-world-premiere-at-toronto-international-film-festival-2019/articleshow/70354747.cms |title=Priyanka Chopra's 'The Sky is Pink' set for world premiere at Toronto International Film Festival 2019 |date=24 July 2019 |website=Times of India |access-date=24 July 2019}}</ref> The film is set to have its world digital premiere on [[Netflix]] on the 11th December.<ref>url=https://twitter.com/NetflixIndia/status/1201812777364410368</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical response ===\nThe film received generally positive reviews.<ref name=ibtimes.co.in>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sky-pink-movie-review-rating-critics-cant-stop-praising-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-starrer-806940|title=Sky Is Pink movie review and rating: Critics can't stop praising Priyanka Chopra-Farhan Akhtar starrer|first=Suparno|last=Sarkar|date=10 October 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-box-office-collection-day-1-priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhtars-film-gets-a-slow-star-2115790|title=The Sky Is Pink Box Office Collection Day 1: Priyanka Chopra And Farhan Akhtar's Film Gets A Slow Start|website=NDTV.com}}</ref> On the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds a rating of 71% based on 17 reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 6/10.<ref name=\"rotten:cr0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_sky_is_pink|title=THE SKY IS PINK|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango Media]]|accessdate=17 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nDevesh Sharma of ''[[Filmfare]]'' rated the film four stars out of five, lauding the film's ability to make viewers laugh despite its tragic undertone. He concluded, writing \"this bitter-sweet film will make you laugh, will make you cry and will surely make you ruminate on the glorious uncertainty of life.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/reviews/bollywood-movies/movie-review-the-sky-is-pink-36641.html|title=Movie Review: The Sky Is Pink|website=filmfare.com}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Mid Day]]'', film critic [[Mayank Shekhar]] rated the film with three and half stars out of five, praising Bose for telling an \"astonishingly dark personal story with reasonable hope\" that never felt exploitative or manipulative. He complemented the \"smart\" screenplay which he felt was structured to dive viewers \"deeper and deeper\" into the characters and circumstances on screen.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-cry-bucket-loads-cant-help/21877166|title=The Sky is Pink Movie Review: Cry bucket-loads; can't help|date=10 October 2019|website=mid-day}}</ref> Priyanka Sinha Jha of ''[[CNN-News18]]'', praising Chopra Jonas, Akhtar and Wasim for their performances, and wrote, \"The real hero in this instance, however, would have to be the zany uplifting story and to that effect, with ''The Sky is Pink'', Bose delivers a fitting salutation to life.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-film-is-all-shades-of-life-2340281.html |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: Priyanka Chopra-Farhan Akhtar Film is All Shades of Life |last=Sinha Jha |first=Priyanka |date=10 October 2019 |work=CNN-News18 |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Writing for ''[[NDTV]]'' [[Saibal Chatterjee]], rated the film with three and half stars out of five, and praised Bose for her direction and writing.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-priyanka-chopra-lends-this-unmissable-film-a-starry-edge-3-5-stars-out-2114432 |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: Priyanka Chopra Lends This Unmissable Film A Starry Edge |last=Chatterjee |first=Saibal |date=10 October 2019 |website=NDTV |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Sreeparna Sengupta of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave the film three and half stars out of five, praising the performances of Chopra Jonas, Akhtar and Wasim, she noted that the film scored high on the emotional quotient. She opined that though the film was lengthy and screenplay needed more focus, 'the emotional arc' and the 'stellar performances' kept the interest going. Concluding, she wrote, \"''The Sky is Pink'' is definitely a stirring watch.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/the-sky-is-pink/movie-review/71509561.cms |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: An emotional, stirring watch |last=Sengupta |first=Sreeparna |date=10 October 2019 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Teo Bugbee of ''[[The New York Times]]'' lauded Bose for achieving a balanced tone in the film, writing \"The writer and director Shonali Bose bounces from tone to tone, livening the somber subject matter with bright hues, quippy dialogue and an ever-jubilant score.\"<ref name=nytimes.com>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/10/movies/the-sky-is-pink-review.html|title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Review: A Story Told From the Grave|first=Teo|last=Bugbee|date=10 October 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/10/the-sky-is-pink-review-1202178086/|title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Review: An Unusual Grief Drama Obsessed With the Possibility of Life After Death|first1=Kate|last1=Erbland|first2=Kate|last2=Erbland|date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Rajeev Masand]] criticised the film's \"blatant manipulation\" but added that \"there are moments that left me with a heavy heart\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rajeevmasand.com/reviews/our-films/pain-relief-2/|title=Pain relief|first=Rajeev|last=Masand|website=RajeevMasand.com|date=11 October 2019}}</ref> Dennis Harvey of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' too disliked the film and wrote that the \"somewhat bland polish on all levels doesn\u2019t much assist the raw pain that should be at this story\u2019s center\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/the-sky-is-pink-review-1203336082/|title=Toronto Film Review: \u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019|first=Dennis|last=Harvey|work=Variety|date=18 September 2019}}</ref> Vinayak Chakraborty of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]'' rated the film with three stars out of five, criticizing the \"flashback-driven storyline\" and its runtime which he felt was too long at nearly two and half hours. However, he opined that the film still works with all its flaws.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/the-sky-is-pink-sensitive-but-soppy-ians-review-rating-/1637218|title=''The Sky Is Pink'': Sensitive but Soppy (IANS Review; Rating: ***)|website=Out look India}}</ref> [[Anupama Chopra]] of ''[[Film Companion]]'' found the film to be \"sensitive\" but highly \"sanitized\". She wrote \"The Sky is Pink is sincere and heartfelt but it never gets raw or messy.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-by-anupama-chopra-farhan-akhtar-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim|title=The Sky Is Pink Review By Anupama Chopra: A Sincere Yet Sanitised Look At Extreme Anguish|date=11 October 2019}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' rated the film with two stars out of five. According to her, the film only occasionally worked. She opined the film felt \"both constructed and sentimental\", writing \"With the material at hand, you expect a legitimate heart-breaker but this one left me mostly unmoved.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-rating-priyanka-chopra-6061269/|title=The Sky Is Pink movie review: The colour barely seeps into the film|date=11 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''The Sky Is Pink'' collected {{INR}}2.50 crore on the opening day, {{INR}}4.00 crore on the second day, and {{INR}}4.20 on the third day, taking its opening weekend collection to {{INR}}10.70 crore in India. Film earned {{INR}}15.15 crore in its first week.\n\n{{As of|2019|10|24}}, with a gross of {{INR}}23.85 crore in India and {{INR}}10.56 crore overseas, the film has a worldwide gross collection of {{INR}}34.41 crore. It did not perform well at the box office.<ref>{{Cite news |author=Tuteja, Joginder|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhars-the-sky-is-pink-a-commercial-flop-that-deserves-better-4549841.html |title=Priyanka Chopra and Farhan Akhar\u2019s The Sky Is Pink - A commercial flop that deserves better |date=19 October 2019 |work=Money Control |access-date=19 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Award\n!scope=\"col\"| Date of ceremony{{efn|Date is linked to the article about the awards held that year, wherever possible.}}\n!scope=\"col\"| Category\n!scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n!scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\" | [[Filmfare Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[65th Filmfare Awards|15 February 2020]]\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Chopra|[[Priyanka Chopra]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards-2020/nominations|title=Nominations for 65th Amazon Filmfare Awards 2020|work=Filmfare|accessdate=3 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Wasim|[[Zaira Wasim]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Film|Best Film (Critics)]]\n| {{Sort|Bose|[[Shonali Bose]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\" | [[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 22nd IIFA Awards\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Chopra|[[Priyanka Chopra]]}}\n| {{pending}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iifaawards2020.iifa.com/|title=IIFA 2020 Nominees|publisher=[[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]|accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Male Playback Singer]]\n| {{Sort|Singh|[[Arijit Singh]] - Dil Hi Toh Hai}}\n| {{pending}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"5\" | [[Screen Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" | [[26th Screen Awards|\t8 December 2019]]\n| Best Film (Critics)\n| ''The Sky Is Pink''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=26 Star Screen Awards|url=https://www.hotstar.com/in/tv/star-screen-awards/s-449/main-event-2020/1260015949|publisher=[[Hotstar]]|accessdate=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Director (Critics)\n| {{Sort|Bose|[[Shonali Bose]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Award for Best Actress (Critics)|Best Actress (Critics)]]\n| {{Sort|Chopra|[[Priyanka Chopra]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Award for Best Actor (Critics)|Best Actor (Critics)]]\n| {{Sort|Akhtar|[[Farhan Akhtar]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Wasim|[[Zaira Wasim]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb title|tt8902990}}\n* [https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/ The Sky is Pink] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_sky_is_pink}}\n\n{{Shonali Bose}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sky Is Pink, The}}\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s biographical drama films]] \n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Films about diseases]]\n[[Category:Medical-themed films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 film directed by Shonali Bose}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Sky Is Pink\n| image          = The Sky Is Pink.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Shonali Bose]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Ronnie Screwvala]]\n* [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]]\n* Kilian Kerwin\n* [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]]\n* Madhu Chopra\n}}\n| screenplay         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Shonali Bose]]\n* Nilesh Maniyar\n* <small>(Additional)</small>\n* [[Juhi Chaturvedi]]\n* <small>(Hindi dialogues)</small>\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Priyanka Chopra Jonas\n* [[Farhan Akhtar]]\n* [[Zaira Wasim]]\n* [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]]\n}}\n| narrator       = Zaira Wasim\n| music          = {{Plainlist|\n'''Songs:'''\n* [[Pritam]]\n'''Score:'''\n* [[Mikey McCleary]]\n}}\n| cinematography = {{Plainlist|\n* Kartik Vijay\n* Nick Cooke\n}}\n| editing        = Manas Mittal\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[RSVP Movies]]\n* Roy Kapur Films\n* [[Purple Pebble Pictures]]\n*Ivanhoe Pictures\n}}\n| distributor    = RSVP Movies\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|09|13|[[Toronto International Film Festival|TIFF]]|2019|10|11|df=y|India}}\n| runtime        = 143 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/sky-pink-2019|title=The Sky Is Pink (2019)|publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=10 October 2019}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = \n| gross          = {{Estimation}} {{INR}}34.41 crore<ref name=\"box:bbh\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/box-office/|title=The Sky is Pink Box Office|website=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=25 October 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''The Sky Is Pink''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[biographical film]] written and directed by [[Shonali Bose]]. The film was co-produced by [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]], [[Ronnie Screwvala]] and [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]] under their production companies of [[RSVP Movies]], Roy Kapur Films and [[Purple Pebble Pictures]] in association with Ivanhoe Pictures. The film stars Chopra Jonas, [[Farhan Akhtar]], [[Zaira Wasim]], and [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]]. Based on the real life story of [[Aisha Chaudhary]] who was diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], the film tells the love story of her parents, Aditi and Niren, dealing with their daughter's illness.\n\nAditi Chaudhary approached Bose to make a film based on her daughter. Although intrigued by the story, Bose instead chose to depict the story of the couple from Aisha's point of view, focusing on their marriage and the effect of a child's illness on the lives of the parents and their relationship. Bose wrote the screenplay based on the details she has gathered through interviewing Aditi and Niren. Nilesh Maniyar wrote the additional screenplay while Hindi dialogue writing was done by [[Juhi Chaturvedi]]. Filming took place in Mumbai, London, Delhi and [[Andaman Islands|Andaman]]. [[Pritam]] composed the soundtrack and [[Gulzar]] wrote the lyrics for the songs.\n\nThe film premiered at the [[44th Toronto International Film Festival]] on 13 September 2019. It was released worldwide on 11 October 2019. ''The Sky Is Pink'' received generally positive reviews, with praise directed towards Bose's writing and direction and the performances. It did not perform well at the box office, grossing {{INR}}34.41 crore worldwide. The film received three [[Filmfare Awards]] nominations: [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Film|Best Film (Critics)]], [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] for Chopra Jonas and [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]] for Wasim.\n\n== Plot ==\n[[Aisha Chaudhary]] narrates the story of her parents, Moose (her mother) and Panda (her father) from [[afterlife]]. Aditi and Niren are a young couple who come from two different backgrounds. Aditi is from the posh end of the town, [[South Delhi]], where on another hand Niren is from a grounded middle-class family. The couple are shown to be in love, with \"an active sex life\" as Aisha's narration describes. The passionate and happy couple get married, and Aditi becomes pregnant with their first child Tanya, who dies within months of her birth due to the [[Severe combined immunodeficiency]] condition. Baby Tanya used to frequently become ill and, while Aditi was convinced it was a serious issue, Niren used to brush it off. Niren believed that negligence was the reason Tanya couldn't be treated sooner and blamed himself for the death of his child. As Aditi was mourning the death of her child, she was consoled by a Catholic church nun and decided to be baptised.\n\nAditi and Niren have a second child Ishaan. A few years later, Aditi bore their third child, another daughter, Aisha. They later learn that Aisha was born with the same Severe combined immunodeficiency condition as their first child, Tanya and Niren are heartbroken. After the doctors in Delhi give up on the treatment, the couple go to London where they learn that the disease could be treated by performing [[bone marrow transplant]]. However, they learn that the treatment is very costly. Niren starts working to earn the money while also asking for crowdfunding via a radio station. After several weeks, they learn that several people have donated money for Aisha's treatment. The surgery is successful but Aisha is kept under doctor's watch. Aditi decides to stay in London while Niren goes back to India with his family and his son Ishaan. Aditi grows overprotective of Aisha, over cleaning the apartment and other things to keep Aisha away from any potential infection. \n\nIshaan starts missing his mother while Niren is always thinking about Aditi and Aisha. This also starts affecting Aditi and Niren's relationship as Aditi is always occupied with Aisha and taking care of her. Months go by and Niren goes to London and asks Aditi to move back to India so that their relationship is not affected. He reasons with Aisha on the grounds that Aisha had gotten better and occasional doctor's visit can be done in India as well. Aditi tells him that they have to live here for a very long time as per doctor's recommendation till Aisha's condition is cured. The whole family moves here permanently till Aisha is cured. Niren's career grows in London and he becomes rich and their family becomes affluent.\n\nSeveral years later, Aisha has finally gotten better and Niren and Aditi decide to move back to India with their families. They shift to the outskirts of Delhi and buy an extravagant and massive bungalow. After a doctor's visit, Aditi and Niren learn that Aisha has been diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], a side effect of the chemotherapy that was done to cure the previous disease. With less time on Aisha's life, Aditi sets out to fulfill all of Aisha's dreams such as adopting a pet (which Aditi did not allow due to the risk of infection), seeing the aquatic life and writing a book, among other things. As Aisha's condition worsens, Aditi grows more and more overprotective and due to over stress, suffers a psychotic breakdown and is hospitalized. Aditi does everything in her power to make sure Aisha gets to see the first copy of her book before she dies. Later, Aisha passes away.\n\nAfter the death of Aisha, Aditi and Niren's relationship is strained. While living together, they grow apart and are constantly fighting with each other. Aditi still cannot accept Aisha's death and constantly brings her in their fights. At a party, Niren shows Aisha's secret video that he had found, a video she had made about her parents. Niren wants Aditi to move with him to London so that she can forget Aisha which she finds insulting as she does not want to let Aisha's memories fade, particularly the house. With anger, Niren leaves for London while Aditi stays back. Aditi later goes to meet Niren in London and they reconcile.\n\n== Cast ==\nThe cast has been listed below:<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/cast/|title=The Sky Is Pink||publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]] as Aditi Chaudhary\n* [[Farhan Akhtar]] as Niren Chaudhary\n* [[Zaira Wasim]] as [[Aisha Chaudhary]]\n* [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]] as Ishaan Chaudhary\n* Vidhaan Sharma as Young Ishaan\n* Manas Mittal as Anshu Tandon\n* Rajshri Deshpande as Anita Tandon\n* Lushin Dubey as Mrs. Tandon\n* Sunil Chitkara as Mr. Chaudhary\n* Nirupama Verma as Mrs. Chaudhary\n* Puja Sarup as Mohini\n* Gurpal Singh as Rj Arjun Gill\n* Sheena Khalid as Rita\n* Sudhanva Deshpande as Dr. Nirvick Gulati\n* Manisha Chudasama as Santoshi\n* Paras Rattan Sharda as Jeet\n* Salmin Sheriff as Dr. Batliwala\n* Rishi Deshpande as Tanya\u2019s Doctor\n* Virhi as Baby Tanya\n* Mala Hashmi as Christian Woman\n* Akshay Joshi as Store Assistant\n* Nargis Nandal as Pilot\n* Raabia Marici as Ishaan\u2019s Girlfriend\n{{Div col end}}\n\n== Production ==\n===Development and writing===\nThe production of the film started when [[Aisha Chaudhary]]'s mother Aditi approached [[Shonali Bose]] to make a film about her daughter. Chaudhary had seen the trailer of Bose's last film ''[[Margarita with a Straw]]'' (2015) thirty times and was eager to watch the film, saying \"I hope I live to see this film.\"<ref name=\"tnie\">{{cite news|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/oct/09/indian-culture-is-better-equipped-to-deal-with-grief-the-sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-2044820.html|title=Indian culture is better equipped to deal with grief: 'The Sky Is Pink' director Shonali Bose|last=Mitra|first=Shilajit|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=9 October 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"th\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/all-cinema-has-an-inherent-patriarchal-ideology/article29410318.ece|title=All cinema has an inherent patriarchal ideology: Shonali Bose|last=Namrata|first=Joshi|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=13 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> However, she passed away at the age of 18 after being diagnosed with [[Pulmonary fibrosis|pulmonary fibrosis]], two weeks after watching the trailer and never got to see the film. Nine months later, Aditi Chaudhary tracked down Bose who was then living in [[Los Angeles]]. Aditi was adamant as she only wanted Bose to tell the story of her daughter.<ref name=\"th\"/><ref name=\"ht\">{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-says-death-of-her-son-end-of-marriage-drew-her-to-the-story/story-otpNEnfTrDPR1OKaNeBWJJ.html|title=Sky is Pink director Shonali Bose says death of her son, end of marriage drew her to the story|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=10 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> Initially, they interacted over [[Skype]]. Later, Bose personally interviewed both Aditi and Niren Chaudhary for eight hours a day for two weeks to gather all the details.<ref name=\"tnie\"/><ref name=\"scroll\">{{cite news|url=https://scroll.in/reel/936799/the-sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-it-is-a-rare-couple-who-survive-the-death-of-their-child|title=\u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019 director Shonali Bose: \u2018It is a rare couple who survive the death of their child\u2019|last=Ramnath|first=Nandini|publisher=[[Scroll.in|Scroll]]|date=10 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> Bose said that \"They talked and cried and healed through the process of those narrations.\"<ref name=\"tnie\"/> Bose had said that she was drawn towards the story as she herself had lost her son so was she ready to explore the subject cinematically and bringing some of her own unique perspective to it.<ref name=\"th\"/><ref name=\"outlook\">{{cite news|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-shonali-bose-on-the-sky-is-pink-har-ek-ka-apna-sky-hota-hai-what-colour-is-your-sky/339168|title=Shonali Bose On \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019: \u201cHar Ek Ka Apna Sky Hota Hai. What Colour Is Your Sky?\u201d|last= Roy|first=Lachmi Deb|work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]|date=22 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> However, she was more interested in telling the story of Aditi and Niren, a couple, dealing with the illness of their child, saying \"I was drawn to the story, not of a heroic teenager defying death, but the parents who had to deal with it.\"<ref name=\"th\"/> Bose said she was \"intrigued and inspired\" by the Chaudharys' relationship, adding \"It is a rare couple who survive the death of their child.\"<ref name=\"scroll\"/> She said she wanted to explore \"what happens to a love story, to a marriage, when faced with the loss of a child\", explaining \"My own marriage ended when I lost my son. 80% of people\u2019s marriages end when they lose a child.\"<ref name=\"ht\"/><ref name=\"scroll\"/> She wanted to make an unusual romantic film and the lives of Aditi and Niren were exactly unusual like the film she wanted to make.<ref name=\"outlook\"/> In December 2018, Ivanhoe Pictures came on board to co-finance and co-produce the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/ivanhoe-pictures-priyanka-chopra-the-sky-is-pink-1203085471/|title=Ivanhoe Pictures Boards Priyanka Chopra\u2019s \u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019|last=Frater|first=Patrick|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=10 December 218|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBose began writing the screenplay based on the narration she had heard from the Chaudharys by approaching it as a love story of two people who fell in love when they were \"only 16 and now at 57 are still inseparable\" despite major tragedies that tear most couples apart.<ref name=\"scroll\"/><ref name=\"outlook\"/> Bose chose to tell the film from Aisha's point of view, focusing on 25 years of her parents' marriage.<ref>{{cite news |title=Priyanka Chopra: 'The Sky Is Pink' Has \"Moments Of Joy, Moments Of Tragedy\" \u2014 Toronto Studio|url=https://deadline.com/video/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shonali-bose-tiff-toronto/ |author=Blyth, Antonia |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=8 September 2019 |accessdate=14 September 2019 }}</ref> Nilesh Maniyar, a longtime collaborator of Bose, had also met Aditi and Niren and wanted to make a documentary about Aisha as he felt there was more to explore and saw Bose's film as very different than his, both projects being in different formats. Since Maniyar had also done his research on Aisha's life, Bose invited him to write the additional screenplay.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/the-sky-is-pink-writer-nilesh-maniyar-deconstructs-priyanka-chopras-psychotic-breakdown-scene-2367617.html|title=The Sky Is Pink Writer Nilesh Maniyar Deconstructs Priyanka Chopra's Psychotic Breakdown Scene|last=Negi|first=Shristi|publisher=3[[CNN News18]]|date=31 October 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"confirms\">{{cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/090718/priyanka-chopra-shonali-bose-abhishek-farhan-zaira-sky-is-pink-script.html|title=Priyanka confirms Shonali Bose\u2019s film, reveals title, mystery continues over hero|work=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|date=9 July 2018|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> [[Juhi Chaturvedi]] wrote the Hindi dialogues.<ref name=\"confirms\"/> Bose wanted to stay true to the real life events and depict them as it unfolded in their lives, without fictionalising or deflecting from actual incidents. She said \"The story, facts and events in the film are completely true. I wrote the script as close as possible to the truth. So, when deciding the look and feel of the film, I decided to stay with realism and be as authentic as possible.\"<ref name=\"th\"/><ref name=\"scroll\"/> While writing the script, Bose met with Aisha's family and friends and inquired everything about her. She also read Aisha's writing, including her emails to her brother and the artwork she had made. Bose revealed that feel connected with Aisha even though they never met.<ref name=\"scroll\"/> In handling the subject, Bose consciously chose to be realistic and avoid melodramatic and manipulative set-ups to express emotions.<ref name=\"th\"/> She said \"I am also very conscious of steering clear of melodrama and exploiting or manipulating you with overwrought emotions. I want you to feel what my characters feel but also give you space. This is part of my film form.\"<ref name=\"scroll\"/> In an interview with [[Scroll.in|Scroll]], Bose revealed that in early drafts, Aditi was the main protagonist as she was written to be the central figure in the story, but later strengthened Niren's role and they became equal in the final draft.<ref name=\"scroll\"/>\n\n[[Siddharth Roy Kapur]] had liked Bose's previous film and had expressed his desire to work with her.<ref name=\"rediff\">{{cite news|url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/report/sky-is-pink-required-big-stars/20191010.htm|title='Sky Is Pink required big stars'|last=Chhabra|first=Aseem|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|date=10 October 2020|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> After the acquisition of [[UTV Motion Pictures]] by [[The Walt Disney Company]], Kapur was appointed managing director of the company of [[The Walt Disney Company India]] in 2014 and produced several films under the new name as he had previously done with UTV. Kapur established his own company, Roy Kapur Films, in January 2017.<ref name=\"rediff\"/> When Bose found out about his new production house, she approached him with the script of ''The Sky Is Pink'' and Kapur picked it to be the first film under of his company.<ref name=\"rediff\"/><ref name=\"mint\">{{cite news|url=https://www.livemint.com/Consumer/vK8fluGeIY8nXR4h4b7RUO/Embracing-technology-is-the-only-way-to-remain-relevant-Sid.html|title=Embracing technology is the only way to remain relevant: Siddharth Roy Kapur|last=Sharma|first=Sanjukta|work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]|date=22 September 2019|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> He said that he found the script wonderfully moving, told with wit, humour, depth and feeling.<ref name=\"mint\"/> As a part of a [[first look deal]] with [[RSVP Movies]], Kapur set the film there, thus collaborating with [[Ronnie Screwvala]], the ex-UTV Studio head, as producers.<ref name=\"rediff\"/>\n\n===Casting and characters===\nThe film's casting news first came out in May 2018 suggesting that [[Priyanka Chopra]], [[Abhishek Bachchan]] and [[Zaira Wasim]] had been cast in Bose's next untitled. The media reports suggested that Wasim was cast as Aisha Chaudhary, with Chopra and Bachchan playing her parents.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/abhishek-bachchan-and-priyanka-chopra-to-play-parents-to-zaira-wasim-1235853-2018-05-18|title=Abhishek-Priyanka to play Zaira Wasim's parents in Shonali Bose's film?|work=[[India Today]]|date=18 May 2018|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> A month later media reports claimed that [[Farhan Akhtar]] had replaced Bachchan and now he would be playing <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-farhan-akhtar-replaces-abhishek-bachchan-in-shonali-bose-s-next-to-star-opposite-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim-2629148|title=Farhan Akhtar replaces Abhishek Bachchan in Shonali Bose's next; to star opposite Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|date=25 June 2018|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> Chopra confirmed her involvement on 9 July 2018 by posting a picture of the script of ''The Sky Is Pink'' on her [[Instagram]] account, revealing the title of the film.<ref name=\"confirms\"/> The official announcement followed the next day, confirming Akhtar and Wasim's casting in the film.<ref name=\"announcement\">{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/farhan-akhtar-may-replace-abhishek-bachchan-in-shonali-boses-the-sky-is-pink-opposite-priyanka-chopra-4702601.html|title=Farhan Akhtar, Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim confirmed to star in Shonali Bose's The Sky Is Pink|publisher=[[Firstpost]]|date=10 July 2018|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> It is the second film to feature Chopra and Akhtar opposite each other after ''[[Dil Dhadakne Do]]'' (2015).<ref name=\"announcement\"/> [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]] was cast as Aisha's brother Ishaan after four rounds of auditions over a period of four months.<ref name=\"saraf\">{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/rohit-saraf-s-sky/cid/1710754|title=Rohit Saraf's sky|last=Paul|first=Ushnota|work=The Telegraph|date=11 October 2019|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> The film marked the return of Chopra to Bollywood films after three years as she was busy with her Hollywood work.<ref name=\"theweek\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/2019/10/03/Priyanka-Chopra-reveals-how-The-Sky-is-Pink-reminded-her-of-her-parents.html|title=Priyanka Chopra reveals how 'The Sky is Pink' reminded her of her parents|author=[[Press Trust of India]]|work=[[The Week (Indian magazine)|The Week]]|date=3 October 2019|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> After coming on board the film as an actor, Chopra asked her Kapur and Screwvala to join them as the producer as she believed in the film and wanted to take more responsibility of the film and learn about producing from them.<ref name=\"theweek\"/> Kapur and Screwvala, both frequent collaborators of Chopra (who had starred in several of their films under UTV), agreed to bring her as a producer, thus making ''The Sky Is Pink'' making the first Hindi film to be produced under Chopra's company [[Purple Pebble Pictures]].<ref name=\"theweek\"/>\n\nSaraf described his character Ishaan saying he is someone who becomes the pillar of the family during the tragedy. He revealed that portraying the character was delightful as he got to explore human emotions a lot more than he had before in his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/rohit-saraf-it-was-always-a-dream-to-work-with-priyanka-chopra-1607218-2019-10-08|title=Rohit Saraf: It was always a dream to work with Priyanka Chopra|last=Singh|first=Suhani|work=India Today|date=8 October 2019|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> Unlike the rest of the cast, Saraf was not not allowed to see the documented footage of the Chaudhary family as Bose thought he would not be able to take that well.<ref name=\"saraf\"/> To prepare for his character, Saraf had researched a lot about the Chaudhary family during the audition process. After his casting, he stopped his research and relied mostly on Bose's inputs on her advice and the collaborative efforts of the cast which he said enhanced his performance.<ref name=\"saraf\"/>\n\nSince the film spans 25 years, the characters of Aditi and Niren's looks undergo several transformations as they age. These changes were mostly accomplished by make-up and hair styling.<ref name=\"transformation\">{{cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-priyanka-chopra-jonas-and-farhan-akhtars-transformation-in-the-sky-is-pink/340216|title=Priyanka Chopra Jonas And Farhan Akhtar\u2019s Transformation In \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019|work=Outlook|date=9 October 2019|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> Chopra's hair inform the age of her character; when her character is young the hair is longer and it gets shorter as she ages in the film, short hair at 50. Akhtar's Character, when younger sports curly hair while is groomed when his character matures and is given mustache in the later portions of the film.<ref name=\"transformation\"/>\n\n===Filming===\nFilming began on 8 August 2018 in [[Mumbai]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.asianage.com/entertainment/bollywood/080818/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-farhan-and-zaira-begin-filming-for-shonali-boses-film.html |title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka, Farhan and Zaira begin filming for Shonali Bose's film |date=8 August 2018 |website=asianage.com |access-date=12 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://twitter.com/priyankachopra/status/1027046519424180224 |title=PRIYANKA on Twitter |work=Twitter |access-date=2018-10-26 |language=en}}</ref> The second schedule of the film began on 13 October 2018 in [[London]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bo4YizMgDCM |title=Priyanka Chopra on Instagram |website=Instagram |language=en |access-date=2018-10-26}}</ref> and wrapped on 17 October 2018. It was part of the [[Delhi]] schedule which wrapped in the last week of November 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BpB0xKshQ-x |title=Rohit Suresh Saraf on Instagram: \"It's a schedule wrap for #TheSkyIsPink. Thank you #London \ud83e\udde1\" |website=Instagram |language=en |access-date=2018-10-26}}</ref> The filming is completed on 11 March 2019 in [[Andaman Islands]]<ref name=\":p1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/mar/14/shooting-complete-for-priyanka-chopras-the-sky-is-pink-1950745.html |title=Shooting complete for Priyanka Chopra's 'The Sky Is Pink' |date=14 March 2019 |website=The New Indian Express}}</ref> A song was shot in June 2019 in Mumbai for the film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-to-return-to-mumbai-to-shoot-for-a-song-for-the-sky-is-pink-with-farhan-akhtar-and-zaira-wasim/articleshow/69258603.cms |title=Priyanka Chopra to return to Mumbai to shoot for a song for The Sky is Pink with Farhan Akhtar and Zaira Wasim |last=Lohana |first=Avinash |date=10 May 2019 |website=Mumbai Mirror}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = The Sky Is Pink\n| type         = soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Pritam]]\n| cover        = \n| border       = yes\n| alt          = \n| released     = 4 October 2019\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 21:08\n| language     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| label        = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = [[Chhichhore]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| year         = 2019\n| next_title   = [[Love Aaj Kal (2020 film)|Love Aaj Kal]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n}}\n\nThe film's music is composed by [[Pritam]] while lyrics are written by [[Gulzar]].<ref name=\"th\"/> It contains four original songs and a reprisal, with vocals provided by singers such as [[Arijit Singh]], [[Antara Mitra]], [[Arjun Kanungo]], Lisa Mishra, Shashwat Singh, [[Jonita Gandhi]] and Sreerama Chandra.<ref name=\"itunes\"/> The soundtrack was released on 4 October 2019 by [[Zee Music Company]].<ref name=\"itunes\"/>\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline       = Track listing<ref name=\"itunes\">{{Cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/in/album/the-sky-is-pink-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1482434710|title=The Sky Is Pink (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)|publisher=[[iTunes]]|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n| total_length   = 21:28\n| extra_column   = Singer(s)\n| title1         = Dil Hi Toh Hai\n| extra1         = [[Arijit Singh]], [[Antara Mitra]]\n| music1         = [[Pritam]]\n| lyrics1        = Gilzar\n| length1        = 4:40\n| title2         = Nadaaniyaan\n| extra2         = [[Arjun Kanungo]], Lisa Mishra\n| music2         = Pritam\n| lyrics2        = Gulzar\n| length2        = 4:18\n| title3         = Zindagi\n| extra3         = Arijit Singh\n| music3         = Pritam\n| lyrics3        = Gulzar\n| length3        = 4:09\n| title4         = Pink Gulaabi Sky\n| extra4         = Shashwat Singh, [[Jonita Gandhi]]\n| music4         = Pritam\n| lyrics4        = Gulzar\n| length4        = 3:20\n| title5         = Dil Hi Toh Hai\n| note5          = Reprise\n| extra5         = Sreerama Chandra, Antara Mitra\n| music5         = Pritam\n| lyrics5        = Gulzar\n| length5        = 4:41\n}}\n\n== Marketing and release ==\nA first look was released on 23 July 2019. The poster was released on 8 September 2019, followed by a [[trailer (promotion)|trailer]] on 10 September by RSVP Movies.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=prwUFBsDRLk |title=The Sky Is Pink \u2013 Official Trailer \u2013 Priyanka C J, Farhan A, Zaira W, Rohit S \u2013 Shonali B \u2013 Oct 11 |date=10 September 2019 |website=YouTube |publisher=RSVP Movies}}</ref>\n\n''The Sky Is Pink'' premiered at the [[44th Toronto International Film Festival]] on 13 September 2019, and was theatrically released worldwide on 11 October.<ref name=\"toird\">{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/priyanka-chopras-the-sky-is-pink-set-for-world-premiere-at-toronto-international-film-festival-2019/articleshow/70354747.cms |title=Priyanka Chopra's 'The Sky is Pink' set for world premiere at Toronto International Film Festival 2019 |date=24 July 2019 |website=Times of India |access-date=24 July 2019}}</ref> The film is set to have its world digital premiere on [[Netflix]] on the 11th December.<ref>url=https://twitter.com/NetflixIndia/status/1201812777364410368</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical response ===\nThe film received generally positive reviews.<ref name=ibtimes.co.in>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sky-pink-movie-review-rating-critics-cant-stop-praising-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-starrer-806940|title=Sky Is Pink movie review and rating: Critics can't stop praising Priyanka Chopra-Farhan Akhtar starrer|first=Suparno|last=Sarkar|date=10 October 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-box-office-collection-day-1-priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhtars-film-gets-a-slow-star-2115790|title=The Sky Is Pink Box Office Collection Day 1: Priyanka Chopra And Farhan Akhtar's Film Gets A Slow Start|website=NDTV.com}}</ref> On the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds a rating of 71% based on 17 reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 6/10.<ref name=\"rotten:cr0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_sky_is_pink|title=THE SKY IS PINK|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango Media]]|accessdate=17 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nDevesh Sharma of ''[[Filmfare]]'' rated the film four stars out of five, lauding the film's ability to make viewers laugh despite its tragic undertone. He concluded, writing \"this bitter-sweet film will make you laugh, will make you cry and will surely make you ruminate on the glorious uncertainty of life.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/reviews/bollywood-movies/movie-review-the-sky-is-pink-36641.html|title=Movie Review: The Sky Is Pink|website=filmfare.com}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Mid Day]]'', film critic [[Mayank Shekhar]] rated the film with three and half stars out of five, praising Bose for telling an \"astonishingly dark personal story with reasonable hope\" that never felt exploitative or manipulative. He complemented the \"smart\" screenplay which he felt was structured to dive viewers \"deeper and deeper\" into the characters and circumstances on screen.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-cry-bucket-loads-cant-help/21877166|title=The Sky is Pink Movie Review: Cry bucket-loads; can't help|date=10 October 2019|website=mid-day}}</ref> Priyanka Sinha Jha of ''[[CNN-News18]]'', praising Chopra Jonas, Akhtar and Wasim for their performances, and wrote, \"The real hero in this instance, however, would have to be the zany uplifting story and to that effect, with ''The Sky is Pink'', Bose delivers a fitting salutation to life.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-film-is-all-shades-of-life-2340281.html |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: Priyanka Chopra-Farhan Akhtar Film is All Shades of Life |last=Sinha Jha |first=Priyanka |date=10 October 2019 |work=CNN-News18 |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Writing for ''[[NDTV]]'' [[Saibal Chatterjee]], rated the film with three and half stars out of five, and praised Bose for her direction and writing.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-priyanka-chopra-lends-this-unmissable-film-a-starry-edge-3-5-stars-out-2114432 |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: Priyanka Chopra Lends This Unmissable Film A Starry Edge |last=Chatterjee |first=Saibal |date=10 October 2019 |website=NDTV |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Sreeparna Sengupta of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave the film three and half stars out of five, praising the performances of Chopra Jonas, Akhtar and Wasim, she noted that the film scored high on the emotional quotient. She opined that though the film was lengthy and screenplay needed more focus, 'the emotional arc' and the 'stellar performances' kept the interest going. Concluding, she wrote, \"''The Sky is Pink'' is definitely a stirring watch.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/the-sky-is-pink/movie-review/71509561.cms |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: An emotional, stirring watch |last=Sengupta |first=Sreeparna |date=10 October 2019 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Teo Bugbee of ''[[The New York Times]]'' lauded Bose for achieving a balanced tone in the film, writing \"The writer and director Shonali Bose bounces from tone to tone, livening the somber subject matter with bright hues, quippy dialogue and an ever-jubilant score.\"<ref name=nytimes.com>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/10/movies/the-sky-is-pink-review.html|title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Review: A Story Told From the Grave|first=Teo|last=Bugbee|date=10 October 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/10/the-sky-is-pink-review-1202178086/|title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Review: An Unusual Grief Drama Obsessed With the Possibility of Life After Death|first1=Kate|last1=Erbland|first2=Kate|last2=Erbland|date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Rajeev Masand]] criticised the film's \"blatant manipulation\" but added that \"there are moments that left me with a heavy heart\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rajeevmasand.com/reviews/our-films/pain-relief-2/|title=Pain relief|first=Rajeev|last=Masand|website=RajeevMasand.com|date=11 October 2019}}</ref> Dennis Harvey of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' too disliked the film and wrote that the \"somewhat bland polish on all levels doesn\u2019t much assist the raw pain that should be at this story\u2019s center\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/the-sky-is-pink-review-1203336082/|title=Toronto Film Review: \u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019|first=Dennis|last=Harvey|work=Variety|date=18 September 2019}}</ref> Vinayak Chakraborty of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]'' rated the film with three stars out of five, criticizing the \"flashback-driven storyline\" and its runtime which he felt was too long at nearly two and half hours. However, he opined that the film still works with all its flaws.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/the-sky-is-pink-sensitive-but-soppy-ians-review-rating-/1637218|title=''The Sky Is Pink'': Sensitive but Soppy (IANS Review; Rating: ***)|website=Out look India}}</ref> [[Anupama Chopra]] of ''[[Film Companion]]'' found the film to be \"sensitive\" but highly \"sanitized\". She wrote \"The Sky is Pink is sincere and heartfelt but it never gets raw or messy.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-by-anupama-chopra-farhan-akhtar-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim|title=The Sky Is Pink Review By Anupama Chopra: A Sincere Yet Sanitised Look At Extreme Anguish|date=11 October 2019}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' rated the film with two stars out of five. According to her, the film only occasionally worked. She opined the film felt \"both constructed and sentimental\", writing \"With the material at hand, you expect a legitimate heart-breaker but this one left me mostly unmoved.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-rating-priyanka-chopra-6061269/|title=The Sky Is Pink movie review: The colour barely seeps into the film|date=11 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''The Sky Is Pink'' collected {{INR}}2.50 crore on the opening day, {{INR}}4.00 crore on the second day, and {{INR}}4.20 on the third day, taking its opening weekend collection to {{INR}}10.70 crore in India. Film earned {{INR}}15.15 crore in its first week.\n\n{{As of|2019|10|24}}, with a gross of {{INR}}23.85 crore in India and {{INR}}10.56 crore overseas, the film has a worldwide gross collection of {{INR}}34.41 crore. It did not perform well at the box office.<ref>{{Cite news |author=Tuteja, Joginder|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhars-the-sky-is-pink-a-commercial-flop-that-deserves-better-4549841.html |title=Priyanka Chopra and Farhan Akhar\u2019s The Sky Is Pink - A commercial flop that deserves better |date=19 October 2019 |work=Money Control |access-date=19 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Award\n!scope=\"col\"| Date of ceremony{{efn|Date is linked to the article about the awards held that year, wherever possible.}}\n!scope=\"col\"| Category\n!scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n!scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\" | [[Filmfare Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[65th Filmfare Awards|15 February 2020]]\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Chopra|[[Priyanka Chopra]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards-2020/nominations|title=Nominations for 65th Amazon Filmfare Awards 2020|work=Filmfare|accessdate=3 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Wasim|[[Zaira Wasim]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Film|Best Film (Critics)]]\n| {{Sort|Bose|[[Shonali Bose]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\" | [[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 22nd IIFA Awards\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Chopra|[[Priyanka Chopra]]}}\n| {{pending}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iifaawards2020.iifa.com/|title=IIFA 2020 Nominees|publisher=[[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]|accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Male Playback Singer]]\n| {{Sort|Singh|[[Arijit Singh]] - Dil Hi Toh Hai}}\n| {{pending}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"5\" | [[Screen Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" | [[26th Screen Awards|\t8 December 2019]]\n| Best Film (Critics)\n| ''The Sky Is Pink''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=26 Star Screen Awards|url=https://www.hotstar.com/in/tv/star-screen-awards/s-449/main-event-2020/1260015949|publisher=[[Hotstar]]|accessdate=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Director (Critics)\n| {{Sort|Bose|[[Shonali Bose]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Award for Best Actress (Critics)|Best Actress (Critics)]]\n| {{Sort|Chopra|[[Priyanka Chopra]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Award for Best Actor (Critics)|Best Actor (Critics)]]\n| {{Sort|Akhtar|[[Farhan Akhtar]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Wasim|[[Zaira Wasim]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb title|tt8902990}}\n* [https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/ The Sky is Pink] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_sky_is_pink}}\n\n{{Shonali Bose}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sky Is Pink, The}}\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s biographical drama films]] \n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Films about diseases]]\n[[Category:Medical-themed films]]\n", "name_user": "Trinidade", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSoundtrack:link to article", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Sky_Is_Pink"}
{"title_page": "Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down", "text_new": "{{short description|2010 single by Alicia Keys}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Empire State of Mind (Part II)\n| cover      = Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down.jpg\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Alicia Keys]]\n| album      = [[The Element of Freedom]]\n| B-side     = We're Almost There\n| released   = {{start date|2010|2|22}}\n| format     = \n* [[CD single|CD]]\n* [[Music download|digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2009\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soul music|Soul]]\n| length     = 3:36\n| label      = [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| writer     = {{flatlist|\n* Alicia Keys\n* [[Al Shux|Alexander Shuckburgh]]\n* [[Jay-Z|Shawn Carter]]\n* Jane't \"J'nay\" Sewell-Ulepic\n* [[Angela Hunte]]\n* [[Bert Keyes]]\n* [[Sylvia Robinson]]\n}}\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[Al Shux]]\n* Alicia Keys\n}}\n| prev_title = [[Put It in a Love Song]]\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = [[Un-Thinkable (I'm Ready)]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n}}\n\"'''Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down'''\" is a song by American musician [[Alicia Keys]] from her fourth studio album, ''[[The Element of Freedom]]'' (2009). It is an [[answer song]] to the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] number-one single \"[[Empire State of Mind]]\" performed by [[Jay-Z]] featuring Keys. Produced by [[Al Shux]] and Keys, the song gained international airplay and download sales although it was only officially released in the United Kingdom as the second single from ''The Element of Freedom''.\n\nBefore its official release, \"Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down\" had reached number four on the [[UK Singles Chart]] on downloads alone. The success of the song from a high volume of album downloads, led to it being announced as the second single from ''The Element of Freedom'' in the UK. The single was released on February 22, 2010.<ref name=\"e.s.o.m.part2\"/> Keys and \"Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down\" are featured on a 2011 [[Hewlett-Packard|HP Beats]] Commercial.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.complex.com/music/2011/02/video-alicia-keys-in-hp-beats-audio-ad |title=Video: Alicia Keys in HP Beats Audio Ad |author=Anthony Osei |date=February 11, 2011 |work=Complex|accessdate=September 9, 2018}}</ref> The song also featured on the soundtrack of the film ''[[Sex and the City 2]]'' (2010).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1637542/sex-city-2-soundtrack-features-alicia-keys-jennifer-hudson.jhtml |title='Sex And The City 2' Soundtrack Features Alicia Keys, Jennifer Hudson |author=Jocelyn Vena |date=April 21, 2010 |work= |publisher=MTV News |accessdate=25 June 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nFollowing the release of \"Empire State of Mind\" in January 2010, Keys stated that she was planning to release a second version of the song featuring only her vocals, as a single the following month.<ref name=\"e.s.o.m.part2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a196200/keys-to-release-solo-version-of-empire.html |title=Keys to release solo version of 'Empire'|work=Digital Spy |publisher=Digital Spy Limited |first=David |last=Balls |date=2010-01-13 |accessdate=June 19, 2011}}</ref> The original takes of Keys' version, entitled \"Empire State of Mind Part 2\", included both Keys' vocals and a new rap verse from Jay-Z,<ref name=\"MTV News\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1625604/20091105/jay_z.jhtml|title=Jay-Z and Alicia Keys Record 'Empire State of Mind Part 2'|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|date=2009-11-05|publisher=Viacom |work=MTV |accessdate=June 19, 2011}}</ref> but the final product did not include Jay-Z.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1627691/20091204/keys_alicia.jhtml|title=Alicia Keys Collabos with Beyonc\u00e9, Drake Hit the Net|last=Aswad|first=Jem|author2=Vena, Jocelyn|date=2009-12-04|publisher=Viacom |work=MTV |accessdate=June 19, 2011}}</ref> Discussing the record, Keys claimed that it acts as a dichotomy of strength and vulnerability, commenting that \"The music is really strong, and the drums are really aggressive, but my voice is vulnerable and delicate\".<ref name=\"e.s.o.m.part2\"/>\n\n{{cquote|I definitely wanted to give my version of it and my vision of how I see New York and how it feels to me. I wanted to do it for my style\u2014more broken down, more on piano, more voice and intimacy\u2014so that's what I did. I imagined, 'If I was able to sing this whole song, how would I do it?' So I just sat down at my piano and I kind of broke it down and started singing about New York as I see it, and it turned out great.|200px||Keys on recording \"Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scotsman.com/scotsmanmagazine/Interview-Alicia-Keys-singer.6029837.jp |title=Interview: Alicia Keys, singer |first=Gary |last=Graff |work=The Scotsman |location=UK |publisher=Johnston Press Digital Publishing |date=2010-02-01 |accessdate=June 19, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110614131635/http://www.scotsman.com/scotsmanmagazine/Interview-Alicia-Keys-singer.6029837.jp |archive-date=June 14, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>''}}\n\n== Critical reception ==\n\"Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down\" was generally well received by contemporary music critics in their reviews for ''The Element of Freedom''.<ref name=\"Christgau\">{{cite web |last=Christgau |first=Robert |authorlink=Robert Christgau |url=http://www.robertchristgau.com/get_artist.php?name=Alicia+Keys |work=Consumer Guide |title=The Element of Freedom |publisher=Robert Christgau |accessdate=April 27, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/12/14/arts/music/14choi.html?_r=1 |first=Ben |last=Radlift |title=ALICIA KEYS: \"The Element of Freedom\" |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=December 14, 2009 |accessdate=April 27, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/mike-ragogna/emhuffpost-reviewsem-alic_b_390623.html |title=HuffPost Reviews: Alicia Keys, Robin Thicke, Avatar, and Pixies, Plus Conversations with Julian Lennon and Precious Composer Mario Grigorov, and more |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |publisher=HuffingtonPost.com, Inc |first=Mike |last=Ragogna|date=December 14, 2009 |accessdate=April 27, 2010}}</ref> Allison Stewart of ''[[The Washington Post]]'' noted that the track, which is a pop ballad, had replaced \"Empire State of Mind\" sports team references and ruminations with \"even milder and less controversial string of generalities\", highlighting Keys' version's lyrics \"If I could make it here/I could make it anywhere\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost2\">{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/12/14/AR2009121403616.html |title='Element' is another safe, uninspiring album from R&B star Alicia Keys |first=Allison |last=Stewart |work=[[The Washington Post]] |publisher=[[The Washington Post Company]] |date=December 15, 2009 |accessdate=April 27, 2010}}</ref> [[Greg Kot]] of ''[[Hartford Courant]]'' wrote that Keys' version \"retains the soaring vocal hook\" but the track \"loses its swagger\" without Jay-Z.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Kot, Greg|title=Review: Album Well-Crafted, But Alicia Keys Doesn't Let 'Freedom' Ring|url=http://articles.courant.com/2009-12-15/entertainment/hc-sc-alicia-keys-review-1215_1_old-school-soul-and-gospel-alicia-keys-kerry-krucial-brothers|work=Hartford Courant|accessdate=25 October 2014|date=December 15, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\nOn December 20, 2009, due to high downloads of \"Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down\", the song entered the [[UK Singles Chart]] at number fifty-two. As of February 14, 2010 it has reached a new peak of number four on downloads alone (her highest charting solo single since \"Fallin\" reached number three in 2001). It became Keys' eighth top ten hit in the UK and second from ''The Element of Freedom''.<ref>[https://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/Brassbound Alicia Keys \"Empire State of Min (Part II)\"] Chartstats. Accessdate=2010-03-13.</ref> It ended up spending eight straight weeks within the top 10 in the country, the longest stay for any of her songs including the original version, [[Jay-Z]]'s, \"[[Empire State of Mind]]\" in which she is featured. So far, it has spent 26 consecutive weeks within the top 40 as well as 52 weeks within the top 100, becoming Keys' most successful single ever. In December 2010 the song was announced as the thirteenth biggest selling single of the year in the [[UK]], surpassing a number of chart-toppers and shaping as the biggest selling non-top-two single with 575,500 copies sold. \nIn May 2011, the song would re-enter the top 100 by jumping from No. 189 to No. 93 in its 76th charting week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/singles-chart/ |title=Official UK Singles Top 100 - 18th February 2012 &#124; The UK Charts &#124; Top 40 &#124; Official Charts Company |publisher=Theofficialcharts.com |accessdate=2012-02-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/62U0sW2kr?url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/singles-chart/ |archivedate=2011-10-16 }}</ref> On January 21, 2010 the single entered the [[Irish Singles Chart]] at forty-six and reached eight.<ref>[http://www.irishcharts.ie/search/placement Irish searchable database search: \"EMPIRE STATE OF MIND (PART II)\"] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/5hFf8iFDu?url=http://www.irishcharts.ie/search/placement |date=2009-06-03 }} [[Irish Recorded Music Association|IRMA]]. Accessdate=2010-03-13.</ref> It also debuted on the ''Billboard'' R&B charts at number seventy-seven and peaked at number fifty-five on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] without an official release.<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=alicia keys|chart=all}} Billboard charts for \"Empire State of Mind (Part II)\"] ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''. [[Nielsen SoundScan]]. Accessdate=2010-03-13.</ref> In May 2012, \"Empire State of Mind (Part II)\" ranked as the 79th biggest selling single of the 21st century in the United Kingdom, as published by the [[Official Charts Company]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Official Top 150 Biggest Selling Singles Of the 21st Century revealed!|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-official-top-150-biggest-selling-singles-of-the-21st-century-revealed-1382/|publisher=The Official Charts Company|accessdate=22 June 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140709102049/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-official-top-150-biggest-selling-singles-of-the-21st-century-revealed-1382/|archivedate=July 9, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\nOn November 29, Keys performed the song's chorus in a medley alongside \"[[Doesn't Mean Anything]]\" and \"[[No One (Alicia Keys song)|No One]]\", on the sixth season of the United Kingdom television show, ''[[The X Factor (UK series 6)|The X Factor]]''.<ref>''[[The X Factor (UK)|The X Factor]]'' [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] Season 6, Episode 26. November 29, 2009.</ref> Keys performed the full version of the song on ''[[4Music]] Favourites''. Keys also performed the song on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' along with \"Try Sleeping with a Broken Heart\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2010/01/11/alicia-keys-places-booty-call-to-andy-samberg-on-snl/|title=Music - New Music News, Reviews, Pictures, and Videos|work=Rolling Stone}}</ref> [[Stephen Colbert]] and Keys also performed the song together on ''[[The Colbert Report]]'' with Colbert adding his own verses on December 15, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.colbertnation.com/the-colbert-report-videos/258570/december-15-2009/alicia-keys---empire-state-of-mind--part-ii--broken-down|title=Alicia Keys - Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down|work=colbertnation.com}}</ref> For the 2010 [[Radio 1 Big Weekend]], the track's chorus was changed from \"New York...\" to \"North Wales...\" and the new version waxes lyrical about all that the [[North Wales]] coast has to offer. Lyrics include; \"Yes, today I travelled north from Harlech to the Menai Bridge. What a pretty drive, with so much to see it\u2019s such a privilege.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/2010/05/18/north-wales-replaces-new-york-in-alicia-keys-hit-91466-26465924 |title=North Wales replaces New York in Alicia Keys' hit |author= |date=May 18, 2010 |work= |publisher=WalesOnline.co.uk |accessdate=June 30, 2011}}</ref> On June 28, 2011, Keys performed the song on ''[[Good Morning America]]''. Keys also performed the song as the final number at the six-hour ''[[12-12-12: The Concert for Sandy Relief]]'' on December 12, 2012.<ref>{{cite news|last=Anderson|first=Kyle|title=Bruce Springsteen, the Who, Billy Joel, and Beatlevana: On the scene at 12-12-12|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/12/13/12-12-12-review-springsteen-billy-joel-kanye-west/|accessdate=17 December 2012|newspaper=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=13 December 2012}}</ref>\n\nThere was no official music video shot for \"Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down\". However, due to the success of the song, leading to it being released as a UK single, the ''4Music Favourites'' performance was shown on music channels as the music video.{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n\n== Covers ==\nUK R&B artist [[Lemar]] covered on the [[BBC 1Xtra]] Live Lounge on February 3, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00qf9f3 |title=Radio 1Xtra Programmes - Max, Lemar in the Live Lounge |publisher=BBC |date=2010-02-03 |accessdate=2012-02-15}}</ref> In June 2014, American artist [[Alice Ripley]] and Ripley The Band recorded a guitar version of the song and released it on their [[SoundCloud]] page.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Alice-Ripley-Releases-Acoustic-Cover-Of-Empire-State-Of-Mind-20140609|title=Alice Ripley Releases Acoustic Cover Of 'Empire State Of Mind'|author=Pat Cerasaro|work=BroadwayWorld.com}}</ref> [[The Bryan Ferry Orchestra]] has performed the song on the album  ''The Great Gatsby Jazz Recordings: A Selection of Yellow Cocktail Music'' (2013).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-great-gatsby-jazz-recordings-a-selection-of-yellow-cocktail-music-mw0002568010|title=The Great Gatsby Jazz Recordings: A Selection of Yellow Cocktail Music - The Bryan Ferry Orchestra - Songs, Reviews, Credits, Awards - AllMusic|work=AllMusic}}</ref>\n\n==September 11th remembrance==\n{{unreferenced section|date=January 2012}}\nDuring football games on September 11, 2011, [[State Farm]] used this song in one of its advertisements. The commercial was directed by [[Spike Lee]] and featured children from [[New York City]]. In addition the full track was listed on iTunes as a benefit to the National Fallen Firefighters Association.\n\n==Track listings==\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = UK digital download<ref>[https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B0034NIRCI Empire State Of Mind (Part II) Broken Down: Alicia Keys: Amazon.co.uk: MP3 Downloads]</ref>\n| title1          = Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down\n| note1           = \n| producer1       = \n| length1         = 3:36\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = German CD single and digital download<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/dp/B003K05PZM|title=Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down: Amazon.de: Musik|work=amazon.de}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/dp/B003M7ZXOG|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130210072600/http://www.amazon.de/dp/B003M7ZXOG|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-02-10|title=Empire State Of Mind (Part II) Broken Down|work=amazon.de}}</ref>\n| title1          = Empire State of Mind (Part II) Broken Down\n| note1           = \n| producer1       = \n| length1         = 3:36\n\n| title2          = We're Almost There\n| note2           = \n| producer2       = \n| length2         = 3:35\n}}\n\n==Charts and 